Feedback:

Sentinel Agent UI/UX Design Directives
To reproduce the modern, "glassmorphic" dark-themed look of the Sentinel Agent dashboard, provide the following directives to your AI model. These instructions cover the aesthetic philosophy, color palette, component patterns, and core CSS implementations.

1. Aesthetic Philosophy
Modern Data-Centricity: The UI should feel like a high-tech command center.
Glassmorphism: Use semi-transparent layers with background blurs to create depth.
Vibrant Accents: Use neon blue and purple gradients against a deep matte background.
Subtle Interactivity: Every interaction (hover, focus) should have a smooth, timed transition.
2. Core Color Palette & Gradients
Backgrounds
Main Page: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f172a 0%, #1e293b 100%)
Panels/Cards: rgba(30, 41, 59, 0.8) (80% opacity slate)
Accents (Blue to Purple)
Primary Gradient: linear-gradient(90deg, #60a5fa, #a78bfa)
Success: #4ade80 (with 20% opacity for backgrounds)
Error: #f87171
Warning: #facc15
Text (Primary): #f1f5f9 (Slate 50)
Text (Secondary): #94a3b8 (Slate 400)
3. Core CSS Patterns (Global)
css
/* Glassmorphism Base */
.glass-panel {
  background: rgba(30, 41, 59, 0.8);
  backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
  -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
  border: 1px solid rgba(100, 116, 139, 0.2);
  border-radius: 12px;
}
/* Gradient Text Clipping */
.gradient-text {
  background: linear-gradient(90deg, #60a5fa, #a78bfa);
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
}
/* Base Typography */
body {
  font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
  color: #f1f5f9;
}
4. Component Directives
Panels & Cards
Structure: A header with a slightly darker background (rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.5)) and a bottom border, followed by a padded content area.
Border: Use a very subtle light border to define the edge against the dark background.
Buttons (The "Ghost" Style)
Default: Semi-transparent background, subtle border.
Active/Hover: Increase opacity, change border color to the accent (Blue), and add a slight scale or glow effect.
CSS: padding: 10px 20px; border-radius: 8px; transition: all 0.2s;
Notifications (Toasts)
Look: Floating cards in the top-right, using the glassmorphic style.
Accents: Add a 4px solid left border colored by status (Success/Error/Info).
Animation: Should slide in from the right with a slight bounce (cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1)).
Charts & Meters
Aesthetic: Simple, flat bars with gradients.
Animations: Use a pulse animation for "active" data points (opacity from 0.7 to 1.0).
5. Layout Strategy
Grid: Use a 2-column grid for large screens, collapsing to 1 column on mobile.
Spacing: Generous padding (20px to 30px) between major modules to let the background gradient breathe.
Constraints: Max-width of 1600px to maintain legibility on ultra-wide monitors.
6. Iconography
Library: Use Lucide React icons.
Style: Thin stroke (stroke-width 2), colored with the Slate 400 or the primary blue accent.

